commitResults.messageBody:
This is because we want to use the filesystem state as the canonical
representation sometimes, i.e. for article storage, which we don't want
to store in memory as the articles can be quite large.

We could simply expose the Storage to the Model as well, but doing so
results in Storage being referenced both from the outside at Logic,
and also from the inside whenever articles have to be added.

Instead we move the entire Storage behind Model for a cleaner
architecture -- now Storage should be an "implementation detail"
that the Model uses to persist itself.

commitResults.messageBody:
When adding strange entries such as pdf files or
https://www.bing.com/s/a/rsslogo.gif, sometimes autofill puts a lot of
invalid bytes into Description. JavaFX is later unable to display badly
encoded text, so it crashes.

This ensures that autofill ensures that it only fills in ascii-safe
bytes so that javafx will probably be able to display them.

commitResults.messageBody:
DeleteArchiveEntryCommand and DeleteArchiveEntryCommandParser classes created to implement this.
Using the same delete command and parser as the list-context was decided against.
The parser needs to return a specific Command object, so if we were to use the same parser, we need to use the same DeleteCommand class for deleting in both contexts.
This means that we have to rely on ModelManager#context to decide which entrybook to delete the entry from.
Could work, but feels very iffy.
